531641\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 15, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rka1665702676713.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rka1665702676713.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rka1665702676713.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rka1665702676713\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA) is a FIPS-approved asymmetric cryptographic\n        method designed solely for generating and validating digital signatures. It provides\n        authentication, data integrity, and non-repudiation, but does not support encryption or key\n        exchange. In this process, the sender signs the message with a private key, and the receiver\n        verifies it with the public key.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Supported DSA Algorithms</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\"> Algorithm </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DSA_SHA1</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\">Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-1 hash function </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DSA_SHA224</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\">Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-224 hash function</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DSA_SHA256</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\">Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-256 hash function</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DSA_SHA384</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\">Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-384 hash function</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DSA_SHA512</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rka1665702676713__table_d3902e1_d3903e1_d3904e1__entry__2\">Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-512 hash function</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rka1665702676713__topic_d25687e1_d25688e1_d25689e1_d25690e1_d25691e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d940491e154\">Generating Keys </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40142e1_d40143e1_d40144e1\">Uniface accepts the PKCS #8 private key format and\n                X.509 public key format. For interoperability, PEM (Privacy Enhanced Mail) encoding\n                is used for both keys. PEM encoding is a Base64 encoding with a header and footer.\n                This encoding is commonly used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40145e1_d40146e1_d40147e1\">You can generate the RSA private and public keys\n                using OpenSSL. For example, the following command generates a 2048 -bit key saved to\n                file named <span class=\"ph filepath\">myPrivateKey.pem</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rka1665702676713__pre_qsl_nnd_rhc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"># Generate the RSA private key in the traditional SSLeay format.\nopenssl genrsa -out traditional.pem 2048\n# Change the private key to PKCS#8 format in PEM encoding.\nopenssl pkcs8 -topk8 -in traditional.pem -inform pem -nocrypt -out myPrivateKey.pem -outform pem</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40148e1_d40149e1_d40150e1\">To generate the corresponding public key:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rka1665702676713__pre_rsl_nnd_rhc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl rsa -in myPrivateKey.pem -out myPublicKey.pem -pubout </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40151e1_d40152e1_d40153e1\">For more information, consult the OpenSSL\n                documentation (<a class=\"xref\" href=\"http://www.openssl.org/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.openssl.org/</a>).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rka1665702676713__section_od5_yzz_ncc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d940491e186\">Example: Signing Messages</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40178e1_d40179e1_d40180e1\">Sign a message by DSA with SHA-256 hash:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rka1665702676713__pre_dp2_zzz_ncc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n  String vMessage, vMyPrivateKey\n  Raw vSignature\nendvariables\n\nvSignature = \"\"\nvMessage = \"This is secret data.\"\nvSignature = $encode(\"DSA_SHA256\", vMessage, vMyPrivateKey)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rka1665702676713__section_elg_xzz_ncc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d940491e198\">Example: Verifying Messages </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rka1665702676713__p_d40184e1_d40185e1_d40186e1\">Verify the signed message:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rka1665702676713__pre_l54_xzz_ncc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n  String vMessage, vMyPublicKey\n  Raw vSignature\nendvariables\n\nif ($decode(\"DSA_SHA256\", vMessage, vMyPublicKey, vSignature))\n message/info \"This is a valid message.\"\nelse\n message/info \"Signature doesn’t match with the message.\"\nendif</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531641\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531641\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 15, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA) The Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA) is a FIPS-approved asymmetric cryptographic method designed solely for generating and validating digital signatures. It provides authentication, data integrity, and non-repudiation, but does not support encryption or key exchange. In this process, the sender signs the message with a private key, and the receiver verifies it with the public key. Table 1. Supported DSA Algorithms Algorithm Meaning DSA_SHA1 Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-1 hash function DSA_SHA224 Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-224 hash function DSA_SHA256 Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-256 hash function DSA_SHA384 Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-384 hash function DSA_SHA512 Digital Signature Algorithm with SHA-512 hash function Generating Keys Uniface accepts the PKCS #8 private key format and X.509 public key format. For interoperability, PEM (Privacy Enhanced Mail) encoding is used for both keys. PEM encoding is a Base64 encoding with a header and footer. This encoding is commonly used. You can generate the RSA private and public keys using OpenSSL. For example, the following command generates a 2048 -bit key saved to file named myPrivateKey.pem : # Generate the RSA private key in the traditional SSLeay format. openssl genrsa -out traditional.pem 2048 # Change the private key to PKCS#8 format in PEM encoding. openssl pkcs8 -topk8 -in traditional.pem -inform pem -nocrypt -out myPrivateKey.pem -outform pem Copy To generate the corresponding public key: openssl rsa -in myPrivateKey.pem -out myPublicKey.pem -pubout Copy For more information, consult the OpenSSL documentation ( http://www.openssl.org/ ). Example: Signing Messages Sign a message by DSA with SHA-256 hash: variables String vMessage, vMyPrivateKey Raw vSignature endvariables vSignature = \"\" vMessage = \"This is secret data.\" vSignature = $encode(\"DSA_SHA256\", vMessage, vMyPrivateKey) Copy Example: Verifying Messages Verify the signed message: variables String vMessage, vMyPublicKey Raw vSignature endvariables if ($decode(\"DSA_SHA256\", vMessage, vMyPublicKey, vSignature)) message/info \"This is a valid message.\" else message/info \"Signature doesn’t match with the message.\" endif Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}